"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-paris-2024-2024-0730-1462709-whats-my-name-daniel-wiffen-olympic-champion\", \"text\": \"  Gold medal and Olympic record for Ireland's Daniel Wiffen... what a night for Irish swimming. Barry Murphy joins Mikey Stafford to try and comprehend a phenomenal performance.  Good luck to anyone trying to get their kids into a swimming class for the next 20 years.  Barry really feels Wiffen's win could be transformative, coming so soon after Mona McSharry's bronze, and more medal opportunites later this week.  We hear from the man himself and plot a location for the Daniel Wiffen Swimming Centre.  Mikey also chats to Olympic sailing silver medallist Annalise Murphy about Sean Waddilove and Robert Dickson's progress in Marseille.  Annalise brings us inside the murky world of Olympic sailing and corrects Mikey's many, many mistakes.  We also hail the inland sailing powerhouses of Austria, Carlow and Blessington.  Listen to the RT\\u00c9 Olympics Podcast on theRT\\u00c9 Radio Player,Apple Podcasts,Spotify, orwherever you get your podcasts  We need your consent to load this rte-player contentWe use rte-player to manage extra content that can set cookies on your device and collect data about your activity. Please review their details and accept them to load the content.Manage Preferences    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"